            <div class="x6 last">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Beltline is home to some of Calgary's memorials and historical parks. Residents use the parks to spend time outdoors with their families, take a long walk, learn more about the community's rich history, or use the parks' recreational facilities.</p>
                    <p>Beaulieu Gardens is an important cultural landmark and a beautiful park with extravagant patterns of spectacular roses. These are formal terraced gardens of the historic Lougheed House, dating back to 1891. The house belonged to Sir James Lougheed and is now an Alberta museum. Volunteer gardens grow a wide variety of vegetables and fruits here as well.</p>
                    <p>Central Memorial Park is a tranquil oasis and Calgary's oldest park right in the center of the community and the perfect spot to enjoy a relaxing picnic amid walking paths, flowerbeds, and fountains. The park boasts of a statue erected in 1924 by the Imperial Order of the Daughters of the Empire to honour the World War I soldiers. The park also has a trail for walkers and cyclists.</p>
                    <p>Haultain Park is another historical park and the site of two historic Haultain schools. Both schools are steeped in history, with one of them being the first-ever school with running water and electricity. Haultain Park has three tennis courts, a playground, and picnic facilities.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Close to the sprawling 17th Avenue retail and entertainment district, Beltline is within walking distance to hundreds of shops, including boutique shops, nightclubs, bars, restaurants, and services, spread over 13 blocks.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Fitness &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Head to the Beltline Aquatic & Fitness Centre for a workout or the four-lane indoor pool for a swim. The facility offers a wide range of fitness equipment in its full-sized gymnasium and weight rooms, a climbing wall, and traditional wooden sauna, and a yoga/dance/martial arts studio. The centre offers fitness classes, including Bootcamp, cardio, yoga, and deep water workouts.</p>
                    <p>Optimal Strength Rage Fitness on 11th Avenue SW is a decade-old wellness studio providing online and offline personal training for those who prioritize health and physical activity.</p>
                    <p>Passage Studio on 11th Avenue SW offers Yoga, HIIT, and spin classes.</p>
                    <p>F45 Training on 4th Street SW is a functional training community that also offers F45 – one of the most efficient ways to burn 750 calories in 45 minutes.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Restaurants and bars &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Beltline is one of the best dining districts in Canada, with over 300 restaurants, bars, and coffee shops.</p>
                    <p>Ten Foot Henry and Bridgette Bar were listed on Canada's 2020 list of Best Restaurants.</p>
                    <p>Park by Sidewalk Citizen offers an Israeli-inspired menu.</p>
                    <p>Donna Mac is the place for your favourite comfort food and some delicious cocktails.</p>
                    <p>Visit Orchard Restaurant for a casual Asian-Mediterranean dining experience.</p>
                    <p>Vegan Street is the ultimate destination for vegan comfort food.</p>
                    <p>The District serves up some locally inspired food from some of Calgary's top chefs.</p>
                    <p>First Street Market is a food hall and bar on 1st Street SW.</p>
                    <p>Proof is a stylish, offbeat cocktail bar offering artisanal drinks and sharable plates.</p>
                    <p>Pigeonhole is a warm rustic yet chic wine bar.</p>
                    <p>Native Tongues Taqueria offers Mexican street eats and some unique cocktails.</p>
                    <p>CRAFT Beer Market and Broken City are two fantastic bars with rooftop patios.</p>
                    <p>Visit National on 10th, Inner City Brewing, and Last Best Brewing & Distilling for craft beer.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
