        <h2>FAQs about Beltline Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Where is the closest hospital?</h3>
                <p>The Sheldon M. Chumir Health Centre is located within Beltline and provides a wide variety of health services. The urgent care center is open 24 hours a day and provides around the clock care for people with injuries or illnesses that are not life threatening.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Where can I get groceries?</h3>
                <p>Co-Op Midtown on 11 Avenue SW is a busy supermarket with great staff and some of the freshest produce you can get in Beltline. There is also a Safeway located on 11 Avenue SW to give residents even more choice on where they shop.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How do I get around the city?</h3>
                <p>Beltline is Calgary's most walkable neighbourhood, and it is also a biker's paradise. You won't need a car to run your daily errands. The public transit system is excellent, with at least 13 bus lines passing through the neighbourhood.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Is there any childcare available?</h3>
                <p>Parents will be pleased to know that over half a dozen daycare centres are dotted throughout the community. So, no matter where you live, you are just a few minutes away from a daycare. Some of Beltline's daycare facilities are Kido Care, Kids & Company, Family First Creative Learning Centre, Little Feats, DH, and Cross-Cultural Children's Centre.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How long will it take me to get to the city centre?</h3>
                <p>Beltline is located immediately south of the city's downtown area. It is often considered a part of downtown. You are just a stone's throw away from the city centre and can reach there in a few minutes. In fact, Beltline residents who work in Downtown Calgary often walk to work.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
